  What is it?
  -----------

  GmailFaxCheck is a Perl script designed for Linux (Tested on Ubuntu Server
  10.04 and up) to automate printing of incoming fax at a [free] fax-to-email
  number and/or of fax-sent receipt from free Faxator service.
  GmailFaxCheck is part of FaxGratis project, which lets you have a completely
  free, full and easy to use send/receive fax solution with Geografical Numbers,
  simply using your PC and a printer.
  (NB: may depend on availability of third party free providers in your country).

  The Latest Version
  ------------------

  Latest version is available as .zip file from GitHub at
  https://github.com/robpower/GmailFaxCheck/archive/master.zip
  or
  directly through git repository
  git://github.com/robpower/GmailFaxCheck.git

